## Refactor proposal for `src/Card.tsx`

The file is a 32-line presentational component with no tests and no sibling components — low blast radius, but high test gap. All three findings collapse onto **line 10's outer `<div>`** plus the nested div on line 24. The fix is to swap the outer element for a `<button>`, route every literal through design tokens, and replace fixed pixel widths with fluid sizing.

### Proposed code

```tsx
import { tokens } from "@/design/tokens";
import styles from "./Card.module.css";

export function Card({
  children,
  onActivate,
  label,
}: {
  children: React.ReactNode;
  onActivate: () => void;
  label: string;
}) {
  return (
    <button
      type="button"
      aria-label={label}
      onClick={onActivate}
      className={styles.card}
    >
      <div className={styles.body}>{children}</div>
      <div className={styles.sidebar}>sidebar</div>
    </button>
  );
}
```

```css
/* Card.module.css */
.card {
  width: 100%;
  max-width: var(--size-card-max, 50rem); /* was 800px */
  padding: var(--space-6);                /* was 24 */
  background: var(--color-surface-accent); /* was #ff00aa */
  color: var(--color-text-primary);        /* was #0a0a0a */
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border);   /* was #cccccc */
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);            /* was 0 2px 4px rgb(0,0,0) */
  outline-color: var(--color-focus-ring);  /* was #1a73e8 */
}
.body { width: 100%; max-width: 45rem; font-size: clamp(1rem, 1vw + 0.75rem, 1.125rem); color: var(--color-text-primary); }
.sidebar { width: 100%; max-width: 15rem; font-size: var(--font-sm); color: var(--color-text-muted); }
@media (max-width: 640px) { .sidebar { max-width: 100%; } }
```

### Change → finding mapping

| Finding | Change |
|---|---|
| **`accessible_interaction_risk`** (`crime_00001`) | Replace the outer `<div onClick>` with `<button type="button" aria-label={label}>`. Renames the prop to `onActivate` so the contract is explicit, and lets the browser provide focus, Enter/Space activation, and screen-reader semantics for free — no manual `role`/`tabIndex` patchwork. |
| **`design_token_escape`** (`crime_00002`) | Move all 9 literals (`#ff00aa`, `#0a0a0a`, `#cccccc`, `#1a73e8`, `rgb(0,0,0)`, `#333333`, `#666666`, `24`, `0 2px 4px`) into CSS custom properties under `var(--color-*)`, `var(--space-*)`, `var(--shadow-*)`. Pulling them out of inline `style` also means future agents extending the file can't copy literal hex codes forward — there's nothing to copy. |
| **`responsive_fragility`** (`crime_00003`) | Replace `width: 800` / `width: 720` / `width: 240` with `width: 100%` + a `max-width` in `rem`, replace `fontSize: 18` with `clamp(1rem, 1vw + 0.75rem, 1.125rem)`, and add an `@media (max-width: 640px)` rule that lets the sidebar collapse. The detector specifically flagged the absence of any `@media` query in the file — this resolves it. |

### Trade-offs to note

- Switching to `<button>` is a **public-API change**: the parent must supply an `onActivate` handler and `aria-label`. If the card's children include interactive elements, button-nesting is invalid HTML — in that case use `<a>` or a `role="group"` wrapper with a dedicated activation target instead.
- Moving to CSS Modules assumes the project already has a stylesheet pipeline; if it's pure inline-styles today, an equivalent `styled-components` / `vanilla-extract` / Tailwind token refactor works the same way — the load-bearing move is "no literal values in JSX."
- The fixture has no `crimes.config.json`-defined tokens, so `var(--color-*)` names are illustrative. In a real codebase, pull the exact token names from `tokens.ts` or the Tailwind config before applying.
